<br>
This is only my second rod but since i am in oasis hunting i figured i would get it while i am here<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyahtzooba.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yahtzooba</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 7:26:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the wheel Oasis Rod</span><hr size=1>  Standing on the shore with the inn at your back and to the right, you can walk into the water and see the tower. Invis and swim out to above the tower and slowly drift down until you spot the rod (can be hard to see), snag it and swim away. I was quite surprised that they did not jump me with simple invis on, very scary moment, very satisfying results...  go get yer rod! /cheer  Yaht, 24th cannon <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukilamyan00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kilamyan 00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/01 12:18:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the wheel Oasis Rod</span><hr size=1> Get wolf form from a druid. Don't use invis.  You become Apprehensive to all of the DWGobs with Wolf Form.<br>
<br>
-Kila <p>.................
[image]www.easydynamics.com/eq/Cat.jpg[/image]</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyahtzooba.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yahtzooba</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/01 7:24:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the wheel Oasis Rod</span><hr size=1>  Apprehensive with wolfform, or indifferent with invis. Your choice... think I'd rather have indiff.<br>
 Yaht <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uorsmoxlorr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orsmo Xlorr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/01 9:02:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> oasis rod</span><hr size=1> NO.  That tower you see with the spectre's is not the tower you want.  The tower you are looking for is under the water.  You will notice how the  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulordbug.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LordBug</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/01 1:08:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: oasis rod</span><hr size=1> Just use invis and come in from above.  Pick up the rod (left-click, not right) and swim to shore.  Bag it on shore.  Mission accomplished, 30 seconds max. <p><BR><BR>
<A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=15011">Ebdain Ahriman</A> <BR>
53rd Renegade Nuclear Technician<BR>
Carassed by the touch of fire<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uiudar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iudar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/01 2:38:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Oasis Rod</span><hr size=1> It is in the underwater tower.<br>
<br>
Wolf for IS Ideal.  Here is why.<br>
<br>
1: Indiff or Appre, either way they aren't attacking<br>
<br>
2: Wolf form has a more or less defined duration<br>
<br>
3: The Gobs *sometimes* see invis<br>
<br>
This applies for both the Lake Rathe, and the Oasis rod.<br>
<br>
<br>
In Oasis they saw invis my first trip.  I spoke to another wizard who was in progress, and he said they didn't.<br>
<br>
I went back a day or two later, and they didn't see it.  Grabbed the rod, it is tough to see.<br>
<br>
-<br>
Same situation in Rathe.  2 visits.  First no wolf form.  The gob in the tower saw invis, but the rest didn't.<br>
<br>
Second trip, guild wedding right above it at the aviaks.  Got Wolf, endure, invis for good measure.  Swam in, they conned indif (didn't see invis).  Got my rod.  Invis dropped as I was swimming away, but they were still apprehensive.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Hope this helps,<br>
Iudar Stoneburner<br>
<br>
<br>
Still need that damn L Guk rod.  Any tips? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uorsmoxlorr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orsmo Xlorr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/01 8:46:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> L Guk rod</span><hr size=1> This is truely the hardest of all of them to get.  Are you having trouble finding the room or getting it out from the room?  I made sure to get this rod on a friday night. Why?  Plenty of people of the needed level in the zone to keep most Mobs busy.  Came into the deadside zone and asked nicely for and ITU and then proceded to head to the room.  Came out of the water and grabbed the rod and gated from there.  Depending on what i pick up between now and when i have to turn in my staff I will probably get me another one just for the bonuses.<br>
<br>
I'm on prexus if you send me a tell i will gladly help you out.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uiudar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iudar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/01 3:55:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> L Guk rod</span><hr size=1> I have accually yet to make the attempt.  I'm hoping to bring the 2 high lvl guild necros with me for backup.  One is a friend, one owes me a favor.<br>
<br>
The problem is I don't know L Guk at all, and have only been to Upper Guk once.<br>
<br>
I'd be grateful beyond words for someone to look at the EQAtlas maps for U and L Guk, and post the approx loc of which zone I should use.  I should be ok from there.<br>
<br>
<br>
I do intend to do this on either a friday or saturday night.  Make things as easy as possible.<br>
<br>
I'm on Torvonnilous, if there is anyone there that can help me, I'm sure I can find a way to show my gratitude.<br>
<br>
Thanks again <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulummanaburn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LumManaburn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/01 9:11:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=265.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: L Guk rod</span><hr size=1> The goblins in Oasis saw thru my invis when I grabbed the rod. Was able to make the shoreline before dieing. The LR goblins did not see my invis. Hope this helps.<br>
<br>
The Hand was camped when I tried for the Lguk rod. I just waited with the group that was camping the Hand (and all of its friends) to pull it. It was a quick run to the room, got the rod and then gated out. At the time I did have Invis to Undead so getting there was fairly easy. That is if you call running by a ton of nasty undead frogloks easy. If you dont have ITU or are not high enough for that spell, bring a friend that has it. Paly, Necro, SK, Enchanter and Clerics all can help you get there. Or you can buy ITU potions.<br>
<br>
The Lguk rod was the last rod I needed to complete the quest. In all I died twice, Oasis and my first trip to Lguk when I got killed in the BR by a train. Looking back I wish I had worked on the quest when I was lower level (started at 35, finished at 40).  In all, it was perhaps the best quest I have ever done both by the challenge and reward.   <p><center>
Luminea Manaburn <BR>
52 Channeler<BR>
Drunks of Tunare <BR>

